                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17651385" author="krummas" created="Thu, 22 Dec 2022 18:53:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this affects any of our current &lt;tt&gt;SSTableMultiWriter&lt;/tt&gt; implementations right? &lt;tt&gt;RangeAwareSSTableWriter&lt;/tt&gt; creates a new collector for every new sstable and &lt;tt&gt;SimpleSSTableMultiWriter&lt;/tt&gt; only creates a single new sstable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17651500" author="blambov" created="Fri, 23 Dec 2022 06:11:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right, this currently isn&apos;t a problem here, only something to be aware of and fix / work around when a compaction strategy needs to split the flush output.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was thinking per-disk splitting on flush can trigger this, but that&apos;s handled inside the flushing code rather than in the writer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
